I went to this clinic a few years ago to have my teeth checked, cleaned and get my sensitive tooth fixed. The reason I went there was I couldn't seem to find any dentist in Penang that could treat my abrasion after my varnish treatment that I did with my dentist in PJ thinned after 4 years. So I got a filling for my cavity, and filling for my abrasion. Personally I wasn't really happy with the white filling on my front tooth instead of the colourless varnish. Treatment wasn't cheap and the filling came out after one year. What really got to me was the fact that my regular dentist had to remove the remains of the fillings before he could put in new fillings and the removal of the remaining fillings on my sensitive tooth really set me off!!! This dentist did inform me the existence of one molar at the back of my mouth that I neglected but never offer any feasible solution other than just to brush my teeth. Charging standard price for sloppy dental work that I have to pay for other dentists to clean up.
I do NOT recommend this dental clinic to anyone.
Fast forward now, I got my teeth cleaned, polished, cavities fixed, a small toothbrush to brush my molar and a retainer for my bruxism (which was the other contributor to my cavities). I also learned not to trust any dental clinic just because they called themselves "dental surgery".

Only one of my teeth was misaligned inward, while the rest were fairly straight. Since I couldn‚Äôt extract any teeth, I first consulted the dentist to ask if I could still get braces. Eventually, I got my braces removed. At that moment, I didn‚Äôt notice anything unusual, but later I realized that the previously recessed area had shifted forward. It‚Äôs not obvious unless you look closely or take a photo ‚Äî then you can clearly see the asymmetry. My mouth looks crooked now.

reviews.text: I have done quite a few of root canal treatments with Dr Tee. One might expect minor discomfort during treatment and it was a pain free procedure. The root canal treatment price is extremely high over here with no guarantee success, so if you have a lower budget, it is better to seek other dental professionals with a more reasonable price. And, in my experience as someone who had done seven root canal treatments, root canal treatment procedure is very hard, highly complicated, pricey with no guarantee success.
